OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWorkers on Real Living Wage
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsee 10% pay rise           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Hundreds of thousands of UK workers    
OL,6, will see a 10% pay rise from Tuesday,  
OL,7, because their employer is signed up to 
OL,8, the voluntary Real Living Wage scheme. 
OL,10,FThe rise would be a "lifeline" for     
OL,11,Flow-paid workers, the Living Wage      
OL,12,FFoundation said.                       
OL,14,FEmployers can choose to pay real living
OL,15,Fwage, a rate that is higher than the   
OL,16,Fgovernment-set minimum wage.           
OL,18,FBut the British Chambers of Commerce   
OL,19,Fsaid there was "a limit to how much new
OL,20,Fcost firms can absorb".                
